My DevSecOps Roadmap & Checklist

Phase 1: Solidifying the Foundations

[ ] Master Scripting: Deepen Python skills specifically for automation and API interaction.
[ ] System Administration: Master Linux command-line, file permissions, and bash scripting.
[ ] Networking: Understand TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP/S, and how firewalls operate.

Phase 2: Cloud & Container Security

[ ] Docker Security: Learn how to write secure Dockerfiles, manage image vulnerabilities, and implement least privilege for containers.
[ ] AWS Security Fundamentals: Study IAM (Identity and Access Management), VPC security groups, and S3 bucket policies.

Phase 3: CI/CD & Automation Tools

[ ] Version Control: Secure GitHub repositories and manage secrets effectively.
[ ] Pipeline Security: Integrate SAST (Static Application Security Testing) and DAST (Dynamic Application Security Testing) tools into GitHub Actions.

Phase 4: Certifications & Hands-on Labs

[ ] Labs: Complete the "DevSecOps" and "Web Fundamentals" paths on TryHackMe.
[ ] Certifications: Aim for foundational certs like the AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, eventually targeting the AWS Certified Security - Specialty.
